{{Italic title}} '''''Revue indépendante''''' is a French symbolist journal.<ref>{{cite book|author=Vladimir Tumanov|title=Mind Reading: Unframed Interior Monologue in European Fiction|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JbwPlydE4wQC&pg=PA55|accessdate=2 August 2013|year=1997|publisher=Rodopi|isbn=9789042001473|page=55ff}}</ref> The journal was founded in 1841 by [[George Sand]], [[Pierre Leroux]], and [[Louis Viardot]],<ref name=sand>{{cite news|title=George Sand|url=http://revueindependante.over-blog.com/2014/02/ch%C3%A8res-lectrices-et-chers-lecteurs-la-revue-ind%C3%A9pendante-vous-souhaite-la-bienvenue-dans-la-poursuite-de-ses-parutions-et-le-pr%C3%A9s|accessdate=4 September 2016|work=Revue indépendante|date=30 March 2014|language=French}}</ref> and is notable for having published such novels as ''[[Les Lauriers sont coupés]]'' by [[Édouard Dujardin]], ''[[En rade]]'' by [[Joris-Karl Huysmans]], and ''[[Consuelo (novel)|Consuelo]]'' by [[George Sand]]. The magazine is based in Paris.<ref>{{cite web|title=Guide to the European Nineteenth-Century Rare Journals at the Zimmerli Art Museum at Rutgers University|url=http://www.zimmerlimuseum.rutgers.edu/finding-aid-nineteenth-c-journals|work=Zimmerli Art Museum at Rutgers University|accessdate=25 October 2015|date=March 2013}}</ref> In 1947 it became the official magazine of the Union of Journalists and Writers.<ref name="sand"/> Its [[editor-in-chief]] is Christian Grégoire.<ref name=sand/> In March 2014 it went on online.<ref name="sand"/>
